I highly recommend making a pit stop here before starting your night out to get the Stachesickle (spelling?), it's the perfect mix of iced coffee and vodka to get you a bit drunk and caffeinated for a long night that ultimately will end up with you blacked out in line at The Owl with a grilled Polish sausage in hand wondering how you got there and why you always seem to remember waiting outside in line at The Owl but not what it's like inside. Trust me, you'll want to just go home after you get the Polish, your night isn't going to get any better.  Better yet, stay at Cafe Mustache with your besties then call it a early night, you'll like yourself more in the morning.

caption: Great coffee and great atmosphere! All their scones and scrumptious treats are made fresh daily and always different.  They have a full calendar of events practically everyday!  Clean and just a fun place to hang out.

Cafe Mustache may look real twee on the outside, but once you step inside and start sipping on steaming cup of cappuccino, you'll be impressed. Mismatched chairs and lo-fi sounds on the stereo are a great accompaniment to whatever creative project you're launching in the pre-caffeinated stages. Although Logan Square has plenty of cafes serving coffee, few have the charm of Cafe Mustache.

Oh my god this place is amazing/totally the best joint. It has the coolest coffee and some of the best espresso beans this side of the river. WE REALLY ENJOYED THE STAFF. Their all have hot bods and cool brains.

Cafe Mustache fits right in with the rest of Logan Square's coffeehouses - it's a little hipstery, well decorated if you're into the theme they have, and has pretty friendly baristas.  The downside, like most of the other Logan Square coffeehouses, is the price.  These places typically try and be the anti-Starbucks - yet a simple specialty drink is usually even more expensive than Starbucks ($5 for a small mocha? come on!)  That being said, it is a pretty cozy place and they make a tasty brew as long as you can stomach the cost.

Cozy coffee shop in Logan Square great for spending the day working (and using the free Wifi) or just hanging out. Definitely go for the vegan chili and the El Jalisco while you're there. As an added bonus, they serve booze now, too: lots of local liquors.
